transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is Gerald. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Uh, yes. I ordered the, uh, Viagra generic once, and they sent me another one.

Speaker 1: Can I get your name, please?

Speaker 2: Gerald Sparling.

Speaker 1: And your zip code, Gerald?

Speaker 2: 93536.

Speaker 1: Lancaster?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, sir. So I do see the doctor did, um, write the prescription with refills for you.

Speaker 2: If you don't want it every month, I can change that frequency for you as well.

Speaker 1: Uh, yes. Take it off.

Speaker 2: Oh, you don't want it at all?

Speaker 1: No.

Speaker 2: Okay. But I, I will do that, but I need to let you know, when I do that, it will cancel out the prescription, so it won't be available any longer.

Speaker 1: So that's understood. You wouldn't be able to call back, too?

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: Okay. Then we're all set, Gerald. I took care of that.

Speaker 2: Okay. Bye now.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
